---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { APPS, SEGMENTS, USE_CASES, description, pageTitle, siteFromHost } from '../content';
const site = siteFromHost();
const path = '';
const title = pageTitle(site, path);
const desc = description(site, path);
const recommended = APPS.filter(a => a.channels.includes(site.channel) || a.channels.includes('marketing')).slice(0,10);
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path="/">
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-cyan-900/10 bg-[#eefdfa] py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_20%_20%,#67e8f9_0,transparent_30%),radial-gradient(circle_at_80%_10%,#a7f3d0_0,transparent_26%),linear-gradient(135deg,#ecfeff,#f0fdfa_45%,#fff)]"></div>
    <div class="container relative grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_.95fr] lg:items-center">
      <div>
        <span class="badge">Operator-built research desk · updated for 2026</span>
        <h1 class="hero-title mt-6">Shopify email marketing tools for stores that want a real retention operating system</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-xl text-slate-700">{site.heroPromise} This rebuilt guide treats email marketing as a merchandising discipline: audience capture, lifecycle timing, product storytelling, cart recovery, post-purchase education, replenishment, loyalty, and revenue analytics all need to work together instead of living in separate campaign folders.</p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apps">Compare the app shortlist</a><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/guides">Read the selection playbook</a></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card bg-white/85 p-0">
        <div class="border-b border-cyan-900/10 p-6"><div class="text-sm font-black uppercase tracking-[.22em] text-cyan-800">Retention stack briefing</div><h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-black text-slate-950">The best platform is the one that makes weekly lifecycle work unavoidable.</h2></div>
        <div class="grid gap-0 divide-y divide-cyan-900/10">
          <div class="p-6"><strong>1. Data depth.</strong><p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Shopify events, products, order history, discount behavior, consent, and customer tags must be usable without exporting CSVs.</p></div>
          <div class="p-6"><strong>2. Campaign craft.</strong><p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Email marketing tools should help a team write product-led messages, not merely schedule generic blasts.</p></div>
          <div class="p-6"><strong>3. Revenue quality.</strong><p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">{site.bestOverallReason}</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-16">
    <div class="mb-8 max-w-3xl"><span class="badge">Ranked shortlist</span><h2 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight">Top Shopify email marketing tools to evaluate first</h2><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">This ranking favors tools that can support a complete retention calendar: acquisition forms, welcome offers, educational drips, cart and browse recovery, customer segmentation, post-purchase care, and winback measurement.</p></div>
    <div class="grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">{recommended.map((app, i) => <a class="card group" href={`/apps/${app.slug}`}><div class="flex items-center justify-between"><div class="text-sm font-black text-cyan-800">#{i+1}</div><span class="rounded-full bg-cyan-50 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-bold text-cyan-900">{app.category}</span></div><h3 class="mt-4 text-2xl font-black text-slate-950 group-hover:text-cyan-900">{app.name}</h3><p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">{app.bestFor}</p><p class="mt-5 text-sm font-bold text-slate-900">{app.pricing}</p></a>)}</div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-16"><div class="container grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[.9fr_1.1fr]"><div><span class="badge">How to use this site</span><h2 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight">Built as a topic map, not a cloned app directory.</h2><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">The homepage is only the briefing. The deeper pages separate app reviews, comparison pages, use-case guides, and store-type guides so a Shopify operator can match tools to actual work. A fashion brand launching weekly drops needs different email marketing capabilities than a supplement brand managing compliance-safe education and reorder windows.</p><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">Each page explains the buying context, the implementation risk, and the measurement model behind the keyword. The goal is to help merchants choose a tool that improves repeat purchase behavior rather than another dashboard that looks impressive during onboarding and gathers dust by month three.</p></div><div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">{USE_CASES.slice(0,10).map(u=><a class="card" href={`/use-cases/${u.slug}`}><h3 class="font-black text-slate-950">{u.name}</h3><p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Use the email marketing stack to {u.job}.</p></a>)}</div></div></section>

  <section class="container py-16"><div class="mb-8"><span class="badge">Store-type guides</span><h2 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight">Choose by merchandising reality</h2></div><div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">{SEGMENTS.map(s=><a class="card" href={`/for/${s.slug}`}><h3 class="text-xl font-black">{s.name}</h3><p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Email marketing decisions change when the store is managing {s.pain}.</p></a>)}</div></section>
  <section class="bg-white py-16"><div class="container grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[.9fr_1.1fr]"><div><span class="badge">Homepage operator brief</span><h2 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight">How to turn this shortlist into a durable email marketing system</h2></div><article class="prose-shopify"><p>The homepage should help a Shopify operator move from a vague software search to a practical retention plan. Begin by writing the jobs the tool must support: capture subscribers, welcome new visitors, recover carts, follow browse intent, educate buyers, time replenishment, run launches, identify VIPs, reactivate lapsed customers, and explain revenue quality. A platform that looks impressive but cannot make those jobs easier on an ordinary week is not the right tool yet.</p><p>Then inspect the Shopify data model. Email marketing tools need to see products, collections, discounts, order count, last purchase date, customer tags, subscription state, consent, and engagement. The point is not to create complicated segments for their own sake. The point is to send messages that match what the customer did and what the store can credibly offer next. Recent buyers should be protected from irrelevant urgency. High-value customers should be treated differently from coupon-only prospects. Product owners should receive education that reflects the item they bought.</p><p>The deeper pages on this site are organized around those decisions. App pages explain tool fit. Comparison pages show where two options differ in workflow and cost. Alternatives pages help teams decide whether migration is worth it. Use-case pages translate lifecycle moments into implementation details. Store-type pages adapt the advice to the realities of beauty replenishment, fashion drops, supplement education, jewelry gifting, food subscriptions, pet routines, digital delivery, print-on-demand trends, high-AOV consideration, and wholesale follow-up.</p><p>Use the content as an operating checklist, not just an SEO directory. Before buying or migrating, rebuild the welcome series, abandoned cart, post-purchase education, replenishment, and winback logic on paper. Define triggers, exclusions, offers, creative promises, landing destinations, owners, and metrics. The best {site.keywordPlural} will make that plan easier to launch and easier to improve after the first month. If the tool cannot support that rhythm without spreadsheets or agency rescue, keep comparing.</p></article></div></section>
</BaseLayout>
